  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\n\r\n### Case1:\r\nIf a desktop user sends a contact request to a mobile user, and a mobile user accepts it, then the mobile user is not displayed in the desktop user's contacts, the contact request continues to be displayed in `pending` requests on desktop, the desktop user cannot be the first to send a message to the mobile user.\r\nThe mobile user is able to send a message to the desktop user, they can continue to chat in 1-1 after that.\r\n\r\n**Steps:**\r\n1. Desktop User (DU) sends a contact request to Mobile User (MU)\r\n2. MU accepts the contact request\r\n\r\n**Expected result:** MU is displayed in contacts for DU; DU can send a message to MU\r\n**Actual result:** MU is not displayed in contacts for DU; DU cannot send a message to MU\r\n\r\n### Case2:\r\nThe same case but DU has also their account recovered on a mobile device.\r\n\r\n**Steps:**\r\n1. Desktop User (DU1) recovers the account with a seed phrase on a mobile device (MU1) (without syncing)\r\n2. Create a new account on an additional mobile device (MU2)\r\n3. DU1 sends a contact request to MU2\r\n4. MU2 accepts the contact request\r\nThe expected and actual results here are the same as for Case 1.\r\n5. MU2 sends a message to MU1\r\n\r\n**Actual result:**  this message is displayed for MU1 as a new notification in the Activity center (`sent contact request`) with a text message that was sent in 1-1 chat; no action can be taken with this notification.\r\nFor DU1 this message is displayed in 1-1 chat normally.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"325\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-02-09 at 12 25 10\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67952253/217800109-2c711035-9f3c-4f20-84f7-72ac6b04b6d7.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: RC1\r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)\r\n\r\n",
